Are you allowed?

756
00:49:46,417 --> 00:49:48,153
What's wrong?

757
00:49:48,186 --> 00:49:49,720
Who said anything
was wrong?

758
00:49:51,489 --> 00:49:53,024
Champagne is for
celebrating.

759
00:49:53,058 --> 00:49:56,261
That stuff,
if I remember correctly
is for forgetting.

760
00:50:01,832 --> 00:50:03,268
You're off the short list.

761
00:50:03,301 --> 00:50:06,137
They found out
about the cancer.

762
00:50:13,711 --> 00:50:16,247
Wish I could say
I was surprised.

763
00:50:16,281 --> 00:50:18,049
It's gotta be against the law.

764
00:50:18,083 --> 00:50:19,750
Oh, what's the law
got to do with anything?

765
00:50:21,552 --> 00:50:23,254
Would have been nice
to be able to turn them down,

766
00:50:23,288 --> 00:50:25,022
but it doesn't
really matter now.

767
00:50:26,124 --> 00:50:27,692
It wasn't gonna
happen anyway.

768
00:50:30,695 --> 00:50:32,563
Oh, Kathryn,
you're scaring me.

769
00:50:41,272 --> 00:50:42,640
I love you.
Oh.

770
00:50:45,776 --> 00:50:48,779
I have to protect my time
for other things.

771
00:50:50,615 --> 00:50:52,817
I can't keep trying
to do it all.

772
00:50:57,888 --> 00:51:00,625
Do you understand me?

773
00:51:00,658 --> 00:51:02,593
I have to give up
the bench.
No!

774
00:51:02,627 --> 00:51:04,295
Yes.

775
00:51:04,329 --> 00:51:06,431
Well, what can I do?

776
00:51:11,869 --> 00:51:13,538
You're already doing it.

777
00:52:28,813 --> 00:52:32,483
I, uh, I heard about
the court of appeals.

778
00:52:32,517 --> 00:52:34,252
I'm sorry.
Me too.

779
00:52:35,853 --> 00:52:37,888
I thought you might
want to have these.

780
00:52:42,927 --> 00:52:44,262
Whoa.

781
00:52:45,963 --> 00:52:48,633
Is this the same bag?
Just hold on underneath.

782
00:52:48,666 --> 00:52:50,535
It hasn't disintegrated?
No.

783
00:52:54,872 --> 00:52:57,708
You know you're gonna
outlive them all, don't you?

784
00:52:57,742 --> 00:52:59,477
If they had
a fraction of your courage,

785
00:52:59,510 --> 00:53:01,612
they would do the right thing
and put you on that bench.

786
00:53:02,680 --> 00:53:04,249
What's the point?

787
00:53:04,282 --> 00:53:06,951
The point is
you're going to fight this.
(LAUGHS)

788
00:53:06,984 --> 00:53:09,487
That's a brilliant idea.

789
00:53:09,520 --> 00:53:12,357
We'll fight it,
we'll take it to court!

790
00:53:12,390 --> 00:53:14,259
We'll make them
give me my hair back,

791
00:53:14,292 --> 00:53:17,395
we'll sue my cancer cells
for non-support.

792
00:53:18,496 --> 00:53:20,631
Tom, listen to me.

793
00:53:23,268 --> 00:53:25,336
My hair is gone,

794
00:53:25,370 --> 00:53:28,205
I have cancer in my body
that won't go away.

795
00:53:29,840 --> 00:53:31,942
There's nothing
you can do
to change that.

796
00:53:44,589 --> 00:53:46,257
I don't know what to say.

797
00:53:47,958 --> 00:53:50,261
Don't say anything
unless you have the answer.

798
00:53:50,761 --> 00:53:51,996
(CREAKING)

799
00:54:00,004 --> 00:54:01,806
Remember the day
on the boat?

800
00:54:04,642 --> 00:54:06,911
Why, we did some
crazy things back then.

801
00:54:08,813 --> 00:54:10,581
It was a beautiful day.

802
00:54:13,451 --> 00:54:16,020
I guess there's just
no following an act like that.

803
00:55:09,006 --> 00:55:10,641
You are so beautiful.

