* Oh, night divine

823
00:57:27,211 --> 00:57:28,613
Let me see.

824
00:57:28,646 --> 00:57:30,815
Oh, Michael,
it's beautiful.

825
00:57:30,848 --> 00:57:32,750
Oh, it's beautiful.
SYLVIA: Isn't that sweet?

826
00:57:32,783 --> 00:57:33,751
Merry Christmas.

827
00:57:33,784 --> 00:57:35,920
Thank you, darling,
it's beautiful, really.

828
00:57:35,953 --> 00:57:37,688
Hey, Mamaw,
I've got yours right here.

829
00:57:37,722 --> 00:57:39,256
Oh, Michael, honestly.

830
00:57:39,289 --> 00:57:40,825
(GASPS) For me?

831
00:57:40,858 --> 00:57:42,159
(DOORBELL RINGS)
Whoo.

832
00:57:46,797 --> 00:57:48,966
I thought he had
better sense.

833
00:57:48,999 --> 00:57:51,135
Mother, we talked
about this.

834
00:57:53,604 --> 00:57:56,040
Hi. Sorry I'm late.

835
00:57:56,073 --> 00:57:57,975
Thought you might
not make it.

836
00:57:58,008 --> 00:57:59,043
Merry Christmas, Sylvia.

837
00:58:00,277 --> 00:58:02,747
Well, come on in.

838
00:58:04,114 --> 00:58:06,250
Michael?
Oh, there he is.

839
00:58:10,955 --> 00:58:12,156
I brought my own tags.

840
00:58:23,801 --> 00:58:25,603
I thought you were
a vegetarian.

841
00:58:26,003 --> 00:58:27,872
And?

842
00:58:27,905 --> 00:58:31,842
Well, isn't there
some kind of law
against vegetarians smoking?

843
00:58:31,876 --> 00:58:35,713
Isn't there some kind of law
against ex-fathers coming
to Christmas?

844
00:58:35,746 --> 00:58:39,249
Yeah, it's probably right next
to the one about gay partners
at Thanksgiving.

845
00:58:41,285 --> 00:58:42,720
I know what
you're trying to do.

846
00:58:43,988 --> 00:58:46,791
I'm not asking you to
do it for me, Michael.

847
00:58:46,824 --> 00:58:49,594
If you want to
work things out with Dad,
that's your business.

848
00:58:49,627 --> 00:58:51,929
Okay, but you have
no right to drag me into
the middle of it.

849
00:58:51,962 --> 00:58:53,631
All I want you to do is try.

850
00:58:53,664 --> 00:58:56,133
Just take one little step
in his direction.

851
00:58:56,166 --> 00:58:59,203
Why? What's it going
to accomplish?

852
00:58:59,236 --> 00:59:01,305
You know,
we've hated each other
for our whole lives...

853
00:59:01,338 --> 00:59:03,641
That's not true.
You don't hate him.

854
00:59:03,674 --> 00:59:05,309
And he has
never hated you!

855
00:59:05,342 --> 00:59:06,644
He said so!

856
00:59:06,677 --> 00:59:07,878
I don't believe that.

857
00:59:07,912 --> 00:59:10,648
He said the thought
of me made him
sick to his stomach.

858
00:59:10,681 --> 00:59:13,317
What?

859
00:59:13,350 --> 00:59:16,754
No, Michael, he might
have felt that way about
something you did,

860
00:59:16,787 --> 00:59:19,156
but he could never
feel that way about you.

861
00:59:22,026 --> 00:59:23,560
What's going on, Mom?

862
00:59:24,194 --> 00:59:25,262
What do you mean?

863
00:59:25,295 --> 00:59:26,764
I mean, what's going on?

864
00:59:27,765 --> 00:59:28,833
What's the rush?

865
00:59:31,035 --> 00:59:32,737
What happened
with Houston?

866
00:59:40,110 --> 00:59:42,212
Houston was an experiment.

867
00:59:45,415 --> 00:59:46,984
When were you
gonna tell me that?

868
00:59:47,017 --> 00:59:48,619
I know, I'm sorry.

869
00:59:48,653 --> 00:59:50,287
You wait until
I'm in a room with Dad...
I'm sorry.

870
00:59:50,320 --> 00:59:52,289
And then you dump that on me?
I wish I could
do this differently.

871
00:59:52,322 --> 00:59:54,959
Do what, Mom?
What are you
trying to do?

872
00:59:54,992 --> 00:59:57,828
Get it out in the open,
the three of us.
No.

873
00:59:57,862 --> 01:00:00,264
No, I am not going to be
a part of that. Okay?

874
01:00:00,297 --> 01:00:02,066
He is trying to take
advantage of you

875
01:00:02,099 --> 01:00:03,868
at the worst time
in your life.

876
01:00:03,901 --> 01:00:05,770
He's trying to help.

877
01:00:05,803 --> 01:00:07,938
He's trying to clear
his conscience.

878
01:00:07,972 --> 01:00:10,107
This has nothing
to do with him.

879
01:00:16,213 --> 01:00:18,115
This isn't about him.

880
01:00:20,050 --> 01:00:22,219
Mom, you're not
making any sense.

881
01:00:30,728 --> 01:00:32,096
Your dad and I...

882
01:00:37,201 --> 01:00:38,736
Your dad and I...

883
01:00:43,007 --> 01:00:47,845
I think we always
believed in the same
things, you know?

884
01:00:47,878 --> 01:00:50,681
I know we did,
I know we did, but...

885
01:00:50,715 --> 01:00:54,685
We never could get there
in the same way.

886
01:00:55,352 --> 01:00:57,722
It wore me out.

887
01:00:57,755 --> 01:00:59,957
I just did not
have his stamina.

888
01:01:04,028 --> 01:01:07,397
When I left,
and you came with me, he...

889
01:01:07,431 --> 01:01:10,100
He became the person
that you hardly ever saw.

890
01:01:10,134 --> 01:01:12,803
So you started to resent him,
that was only natural.

891
01:01:12,837 --> 01:01:15,906
But, Michael,
I saw what was happening.

892
01:01:18,108 --> 01:01:20,277
I saw it and I took
advantage of it.

893
01:01:22,980 --> 01:01:25,750
You were a little kid.

894
01:01:25,783 --> 01:01:29,219
You wanted
a black and white picture
and I gave you one.

895
01:01:33,423 --> 01:01:34,458
You see what I'm saying?

896
01:01:38,963 --> 01:01:41,832
No. No.

897
01:01:41,866 --> 01:01:44,902
All my life
you've been telling me what
a bastard he is, okay,

898
01:01:44,935 --> 01:01:47,404
you're not just gonna
change your mind now.
Michael.

899
01:01:47,437 --> 01:01:49,840
Leave me alone.
Both of you!

900
01:02:02,152 --> 01:02:05,022
I never said
he made me sick.
I know that.

901
01:02:07,892 --> 01:02:10,394
How could he have
thought that all these years?

902
01:02:10,427 --> 01:02:12,429
I don't know,
you'll have to ask him.

903
01:02:14,464 --> 01:02:16,767
Oh, he won't talk to me
about that, you know that.

904
01:02:16,801 --> 01:02:18,936
I'm sure you'll find a way.

905
01:02:22,206 --> 01:02:23,941
You just never let up, do you?

906
01:02:26,376 --> 01:02:28,145
This is so typical.

907
01:02:28,178 --> 01:02:31,348
Mmm. Yeah, this is
so typical...

908
01:02:32,416 --> 01:02:33,818
Of you.

909
01:02:39,156 --> 01:02:40,958
Come on,
let me buy you a drink.

910
01:02:40,991 --> 01:02:43,360
What are you talking about,
it's Christmas.

911
01:02:43,393 --> 01:02:45,195
Oh, I know a place
that's open.

912
01:02:46,396 --> 01:02:48,232
(SLOW MUSIC PLAYING)

913
01:02:50,134 --> 01:02:52,302
Oh. Where did
you get this wine?

914
01:02:52,336 --> 01:02:53,370
Philippe Million.

915
01:02:54,071 --> 01:02:55,572
What?

916
01:02:55,605 --> 01:02:58,042
You hate that place.

917
01:02:58,075 --> 01:03:00,177
Never. I love that place,
I've always loved that place.

918
01:03:00,210 --> 01:03:03,080
Tom, I tried to get you
to take me there for years.

919
01:03:03,113 --> 01:03:05,049
No. No, no, no, no, no.

920
01:03:05,082 --> 01:03:07,017
I have no recollection
of that, Your Honor.

921
01:03:10,387 --> 01:03:12,857
Actually...

922
01:03:12,890 --> 01:03:15,092
I can't remember
a single thing right now.

923
01:03:19,063 --> 01:03:20,998
You know, maybe you're right.

924
01:03:22,632 --> 01:03:24,434
You never did know
how to give up.

925
01:03:26,336 --> 01:03:29,039
And you obviously
gonna get some place
I'll never see.

926
01:03:30,640 --> 01:03:32,877
Don't be so dramatic.

927
01:03:32,910 --> 01:03:35,980
You haven't died yet.
No, but it sure gives me
leverage in the conversation.

928
01:03:36,013 --> 01:03:37,848
You don't really think
I'm gonna let you
win an argument

929
01:03:37,882 --> 01:03:39,950
just because you have
the big C, do you?

930
01:03:39,984 --> 01:03:43,387
Tom, I didn't get cancer
just so that I could finally
win the argument.

931
01:03:44,654 --> 01:03:45,956
Are you sure?

932
01:03:47,191 --> 01:03:48,225
Mmm.

933
01:03:55,432 --> 01:03:57,501
(ROMANTIC MUSIC PLAYING)

934
01:04:03,140 --> 01:04:05,242
You know when
we're really at our best?

935
01:04:05,542 --> 01:04:06,877
When?

936
01:04:08,278 --> 01:04:10,214
When neither one of us
is talking.

937
01:04:12,516 --> 01:04:14,985
What a thing for two
lawyers to discover.

938
01:04:46,316 --> 01:04:48,452
To bad parenting.
Hear, hear.

939
01:04:50,720 --> 01:04:54,158
To a bad marriage.
Ooh, triple hear to that.

940
01:04:55,960 --> 01:04:59,196
To bad in-laws.
Wait a minute, now you're
talking about my mother.

941
01:04:59,229 --> 01:05:02,132
You didn't exactly
get along with
my mother either.

942
01:05:02,166 --> 01:05:03,633
I never met your mother.

943
01:05:03,667 --> 01:05:05,002
Use your imagination.

944
01:05:05,569 --> 01:05:07,237
Ooh.

945
01:05:07,271 --> 01:05:08,605
Hear, hear.

946
01:05:12,142 --> 01:05:13,543
How come you got the china?

947
01:05:13,577 --> 01:05:15,245
Stayed with the crystal.

948
01:05:16,346 --> 01:05:17,948
You got all the good stuff.

949
01:05:19,716 --> 01:05:21,385
You got Michael.

950
01:05:21,418 --> 01:05:22,953
You got the notches.

951
01:05:22,987 --> 01:05:24,021
You could stay.

952
01:05:24,588 --> 01:05:26,623
No, I couldn't.

953
01:05:26,656 --> 01:05:28,325
But thank you.

954
01:05:36,433 --> 01:05:38,568
You know, someday,

955
01:05:38,602 --> 01:05:42,306
it would be really good
for Michael if he spent
some time in this house.

956
01:06:14,638 --> 01:06:16,140
Oh, Daddy.

957
01:06:18,808 --> 01:06:22,012
I've been having
the lousiest dreams.

958
01:06:22,046 --> 01:06:24,181
Hi, Kat.
It's been a while.

959
01:06:37,161 --> 01:06:38,228
Hmm.

960
01:07:38,388 --> 01:07:39,423
Kat?

961
01:07:40,590 --> 01:07:42,326
(DOORBELL RINGS)

962
01:08:06,783 --> 01:08:08,084
Kat?

963
01:08:24,601 --> 01:08:26,536
My baby...

964
01:08:26,570 --> 01:08:28,305
Baby... (SOBS)

965
01:08:30,174 --> 01:08:31,775
She's asleep.

966
01:08:31,808 --> 01:08:33,177
She has two broken ribs.

967
01:08:34,378 --> 01:08:37,314
Apparently the bones just...

968
01:08:37,347 --> 01:08:40,884
(SIGHS) I don't know.
It's either the drugs
or the cancer.

969
01:08:41,785 --> 01:08:42,852
Where's Michael?

970
01:08:43,720 --> 01:08:45,822
Does he know?

971
01:08:45,855 --> 01:08:47,557
Well, he has to be told.

972
01:08:55,265 --> 01:08:56,400
Pull!

973
01:08:59,269 --> 01:09:00,870
MAN: David Vardy, 
 you're next up.

974
01:09:04,674 --> 01:09:06,510
Your mother's
in the hospital.

975
01:09:10,580 --> 01:09:11,715
Pull!

976
01:09:17,287 --> 01:09:19,523
I know you don't
wanna have to see me,

977
01:09:19,556 --> 01:09:21,358
but she wants me there.

978
01:09:21,391 --> 01:09:22,726
When's she getting out?

979
01:09:24,361 --> 01:09:25,395
Michael...

980
01:09:26,696 --> 01:09:28,432
This is, uh, serious.

981
01:09:31,435 --> 01:09:34,338
We don't have to cross paths.
We could work out a schedule.

982
01:09:34,371 --> 01:09:36,706
But if we're gonna do that,
you're gonna have to
talk to me.

983
01:09:38,975 --> 01:09:40,310
Pull.

984
01:09:43,413 --> 01:09:44,948
Not sure I know how.

985
01:09:44,981 --> 01:09:46,883
I want to talk to you
about this, Michael.

986
01:09:47,917 --> 01:09:49,486
I really do.

987
01:09:51,455 --> 01:09:53,257
And I always have.

988
01:09:59,529 --> 01:10:00,664
Pull!

989
01:10:01,030 --> 01:10:02,499
(GUNSHOT)

990
01:10:12,342 --> 01:10:14,878
Sitting on the bed,
that can't be good.

991
01:10:20,717 --> 01:10:22,286
My goodness.

992
01:10:24,788 --> 01:10:27,591
This is gonna be
very hard for you,
isn't it, Irish?

993
01:10:29,759 --> 01:10:31,695
(SIGHS)

994
01:10:31,728 --> 01:10:35,765
Listen. We're both
big believers in the
unvarnished truth, aren't we?

995
01:10:38,968 --> 01:10:40,870
The thing is, Kathryn,

996
01:10:40,904 --> 01:10:44,608
there isn't a thing
we can do,

997
01:10:44,641 --> 01:10:47,010
except keep you
as comfortable as possible.

998
01:10:53,917 --> 01:10:55,819
You can hold
